1.text: Color in brown spots on some yellow origami paper to design the pattern.

2.text: Fold and unfold the paper in half twice to make 2 creases.

3.text: Rotate the same sheet of paper so it looks like a diamond.

4.text: Fold and unfold the paper in half twice to make 2 more creases.

5.text: Pinch and press the paper into a small square.

6.text: Fold the side corners of paper into the center.

7.text: Flip the square over and repeat this folding process.

8.text: Fold the top triangular section of the paper downwards.

9.text: Flip the paper over and lift up the folded section.

10.text: Press the paper into a kite shape.

11.text: Do the same flip, fold, and press on the other side.

12.text: Hold the paper structure upright and fold it in half.

13.text: Fold the 2 side points upward to create a paper hat shape.

14.text: Flip the paper and push the left section of paper upwards.

15.text: Fold the front section of paper backward to form the neck and front legs.

16.text: Crease the back section of paper downwards to form the back legs.

17.text: Unfold the back legs and crease them into place.

18.text: Fold and crease the upper section of the paper neck to form the head.

19.text: Crease and fold both halves of the neck to make it thin and rectangular.

20.text: Repeat this folding and creasing section along the giraffe’s back.
